Algorithm:
1. Start.
2. Input the number n.
3. Define a recursive function factorial(x):
If x == 0 or x == 1, return 1.
Otherwise, return x * factorial(x - 1).
4. Call the function factorial(n) and store the result.
5. Print the factorial value.
6. Stop.

Pseudocode:
START
FUNCTION factorial(x)
    IF x == 0 OR x == 1 THEN
        RETURN 1
    ELSE
        RETURN x * factorial(x - 1)
    ENDIF
END FUNCTION
PRINT "Enter a number:"
INPUT n
result = factorial(n)
PRINT "The factorial of", n, "is:", result
STOP

Flow Chart:
A[Start] --> B[Input n: Get the number whose factorial is to be calculated]
    B --> C[Call Recursive Function: factorial(x)]
    C --> D{Is x == 0 or x == 1?}
    D --> E[Return 1]:::yes
    D --> F[Return x * factorial(x - 1)]:::no
    F --> G[Display Result: Output the factorial of n]
    E --> G
    G --> H[End
